🚀 Recommended Next Platform (Highest Remaining Priority)

At this stage, I recommend building IAM-001 — Enterprise Identity & Access Management (IAM) before any additional business modules.

A modern enterprise platform should have a centralized security layer rather than implementing authentication and authorization separately in each module.

The IAM platform should include:

Single Sign-On (SSO)
Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)
Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
Attribute-Based Access Control (ABAC)
Policy-Based Access Control (PBAC)
Privileged Access Management (PAM)
Identity Governance & Administration (IGA)
Just-In-Time (JIT) access
Segregation of Duties (SoD)
Passwordless authentication (FIDO2/WebAuthn)
Session management
API identity and machine-to-machine authentication
Enterprise audit logging
AI-driven identity risk scoring
Strategic Roadmap Recommendation

At this point, ARTH.OS has evolved into a platform comparable in breadth to enterprise suites. I recommend shifting from designing individual modules to organizing development into platform teams (Identity, AI, Data, Integration, Workflow, Documents, Observability) and domain teams (Finance, Lending, HRMS, CRM, Treasury, Risk). This organization will scale much better than continuing to build modules sequentially and is the approach typically used for large enterprise software products